If it‚Äôs a tight race and the CPC candidate is competitive, then yes, unfortunately you live in a riding where you must vote strategically. This will mean voting for whoever has the best chance of beating the Conservative. This was the case in ~55% of ridings in 2015. Sigh.

I know, I know. You want to be strategic. You don‚Äôt want to risk splitting the vote and somehow electing a Conservative. I UNDERSTAND. So this is where it really comes down to the riding that you live in. I‚Äôll explain:

This is where I think things are getting (deliberately) misleading. We have multiple parties in Canada! Not just two! So in order to not elect a Conservative in your riding, you can vote for... any of the other parties! What a concept!
